The Ruaha Catholic University (RUCU) in Iringa region has invited Italian Ambassador to Tanzania Marco Lombardi for the purpose of exploring cooperation with Italian varsities. Three higher academic institutions targeted by Tanzania’s Southern Highland varsity were Brescia Catholic, Palermo and Turin. This represented an opportunity to visit a dynamic region of the Southern Highland of Tanzania. During his mission, Lombardi met with Iringa Regional Commissioner,  Queen Sendiga, with whom he had a discussion on the state of art of economic cooperation with Italy and, in particular, on the recent Italian industrial investment in Kylolo. The diplomat thanked the large Italian Community present in Iringa for a warm welcome during his four-day mission. The field visits health projects of CUAMM, Sant’Egidio, Co.Pe, ASVET and those in social, training and agricultural fields of Consolata, CEFA, Nyumba Ali and Africa Chiama. Lombardi underlined the important role of the Italian Episcopal Conference, Italian Agency for Development Cooperation and Italian volunteers in the development of a growing region like Iringa.